      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef</strong> and <strong>bacon lardons</strong> to the dish with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2 min or until lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
